[Review] YesStyle January Sponsored Product: SNP Prep Peptaronic Cream

Very basic and cute post for tuhday!!!

Product info:
〰 contains 6 peptides and 5 HA types to provide deep moisture without leaving a greasy, oily feel.
〰 nourishes and firms the skin alongside other ingredients like niacinamide, panthenol, macadamia seed oil, and adenosine.
〰 has fragrance: i'm so sorry but this smells like flowers from a funeral 😭

Things I like about this cream:
〰 cute packaging 😘
〰 relatively affordable
〰 Very nourishing and hydrating as it claims
〰 Doesn't cause me any irritation/stinging
〰 Airy, creamy formula makes it luxurious to spread onto skin
〰 the presence of macadamia oil makes it emollient and provides a slightly occlusive layer
〰 Good also for AM usage since it's not too heavy, but I mostly use at night (I also layer another thick moisturizer after this)
〰 divine inci list 😝💅

Things I dislike about this cream:
〰 the funeral flowers scent which really puts me off 😭✋
〰 not a big deal but has no own spatula (had to use my own)👺

This would actually be a solid moisturizer + the fact that it's really affordable. 🧍‍♀️ but I wanna hear y'alls opinions for those who've tried this: do you like the scent? 🤧

Anyway, if you still wanna try this 55ml cream, you can get it on YesStyle for 13USD (on sale rn at 10USD). Feel free to use my code M0CHISKIN006 for 2-5% off your total purchase 😝😝😝💅💅💅✨✨💖💖✋✋
